WEBVTT

00:02:59.520 --> 00:03:01.640
This idea is taking hold
outside of sports.

00:03:02.480 --> 00:03:04.776
The Head of Design
and Research at Pinterest

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:07.176
told me that they've built
one of the most diverse

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:09.296
and high-performing teams
in Silicon Valley

00:03:09.320 --> 00:03:11.696
because they believe
that no one type of person

00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:13.560
holds a monopoly on talent.

00:03:14.440 --> 00:03:17.136
They've worked hard
to look beyond major tech hubs

00:03:17.160 --> 00:03:19.416
and focus on designers' portfolios,

00:03:19.440 --> 00:03:20.760
not their pedigrees.

00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:24.480
Two: hire for performance.

00:03:25.080 --> 00:03:27.336
Inspired by my own job experience,

00:03:27.360 --> 00:03:30.056
I cofounded a hiring platform
called Headlight,